content.description:
Often overlooked by teams climbing Diamond of San Diego's 2nd pitch, Ms. Tiggers is perhaps the best pitch off The Officer's Club.

Three or four bolts into DoSD's (Diamond of San Diego) 2nd pitch, as you pull under the roof visible from the belay, you skirt the roof to the right, instead of to the left for DoSD. Three bolts climb you onto the wonderful, off balance arete that trends right, into the finishing bolts of Burlman. And finishes at the same shared anchor of DoSD and Burlman.
Easy clipping first few bolts, bouldery 3rd bolt (felt height dependent), cruxy-thin 5th bolt with easier climbing on bolts 6-8.
content.protection: 8 Bolts w/2 bolt anchors & rap rings.
content.location: Start 1 route right of Burlman (2 routes right of Miss Tigers)

content.description: Easy climbing to bolt 1, work through a pod, flake & into the start of the dihedral for bolt 2, climb the dihedral or its arete to bolt 3 on easy/runout climbing, climb through 2 more bolts on fun crimp face climbing to a big ledge, clip a bolt and launch in to the crux for 2 bolts on ramp with techy climbing up to a ledge (take care clipping these two as a fall would put you on the ledge below), clip one more bolt to the anchors.
content.protection: 9 bolts with bolted anchors. You can easily climb through the anchors to other nearby routes with bolted anchors & rap rings.
content.location: Start between pitch 2 of Commander & Diamond of San Diego (1 route left of Miss Tiggers).
